      {
        "step": 4,
        "type": "text",
        "text": "✅ **Counter circuit complete!**\n\n## Wiring Table\n\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| D2 | R_a → Seg7.a | Segment A (220Ω resistor) |\n| D3 | R_b → Seg7.b | Segment B (220Ω resistor) |\n| D4 | R_c → Seg7.c | Segment C (220Ω resistor) |\n| D5 | R_d → Seg7.d | Segment D (220Ω resistor) |\n| D6 | R_e → Seg7.e | Segment E (220Ω resistor) |\n| D7 | R_f → Seg7.f | Segment F (220Ω resistor) |\n| D8 | R_g → Seg7.g | Segment G (220Ω resistor) |\n| D9 | Button.a | Increment button (active LOW) |\n| GND | Seg7.gnd | 7-segment common cathode |\n| GND | Button.b | Button return |\n\n## How It Works\n\n- **Button press detection**: Uses `INPUT_PULLUP` — button pulls pin D9 LOW when pressed.\n- **Increment on press**: Detects LOW→HIGH transition and increments `count` from 0–9.\n- **Auto-reset**: Counter wraps to 0 after reaching 9.\n- **Segment lookup table**: `displayDigit()` encodes the 7-segment on/off patterns for each digit using if/else chains.\n- **20mA per segment**: Each 220Ω resistor limits LED current to ~20mA (safe for Arduino).\n\nPress the button to count: 0 → 1 → 2 → ... → 9 → 0 (repeat)."
      }
